  "planner_system_prompt": "You are a strict Minecraft reconstruction planner. Output only one JSON object. No markdown. No prose outside JSON.",
  "planner_user_template": "You are given a building description JSON.\nCreate a high-fidelity executable build plan.\n\nUse ONLY operation types:\n- fill: axis-aligned cuboid fill\n- carve: axis-aligned cuboid set to air\n- set: single block placement\n\nBefore writing operations, infer a structured geometry spec.\nRequired output JSON schema:\n{\n  \"plan_version\": \"v2_strong\",\n  \"bbox\": {\"xmin\": 0, \"xmax\": 0, \"ymin\": 0, \"ymax\": 0, \"zmin\": 0, \"zmax\": 0},\n  \"palette\": {\n    \"wall\": \"stonebrick\",\n    \"roof\": \"wood\",\n    \"trim\": \"brick\",\n    \"glass\": \"glass\",\n    \"light\": \"glowstone\",\n    \"floor\": \"wood\"\n  },\n  \"structure_spec\": {\n    \"footprint_2d\": {\n      \"type\": \"rectangle|l_shape|u_shape|complex\",\n      \"segments\": [{\"x1\": 0, \"z1\": 0, \"x2\": 0, \"z2\": 0, \"label\": \"main\"}],\n      \"symmetry\": \"string\"\n    },\n    \"floors\": [\n      {\n        \"floor_index\": 0,\n        \"y_range\": {\"ymin\": 0, \"ymax\": 0},\n        \"rooms_hint\": \"string\",\n        \"perimeter_profile\": \"string\"\n      }\n    ],\n    \"openings\": [\n      {\"kind\": \"door|window\", \"face\": \"north|south|east|west|roof\", \"x1\": 0, \"y1\": 0, \"z1\": 0, \"x2\": 0, \"y2\": 0, \"z2\": 0}\n    ],\n    \"roof_profile\": {\n      \"type\": \"flat|gable|hip|dome|other|unknown\",\n      \"base_y\": 0,\n      \"ridge_axis\": \"x|z|none\",\n      \"layers\": [{\"y\": 0, \"x1\": 0, \"z1\": 0, \"x2\": 0, \"z2\": 0, \"block\": \"wood\"}]\n    }\n  },\n  \"operations\": [\n    {\"op\": \"fill\", \"x1\": 0, \"y1\": 0, \"z1\": 0, \"x2\": 1, \"y2\": 1, \"z2\": 1, \"block\": \"stonebrick\", \"purpose\": \"base\"},\n    {\"op\": \"carve\", \"x1\": 0, \"y1\": 0, \"z1\": 0, \"x2\": 0, \"y2\": 0, \"z2\": 0, \"purpose\": \"hollow\"},\n    {\"op\": \"set\", \"x\": 0, \"y\": 0, \"z\": 0, \"block\": \"glowstone\", \"purpose\": \"light\"}\n  ],\n  \"self_check\": {\n    \"bbox_consistency\": \"ok|fix_needed\",\n    \"operation_count\": 0,\n    \"operation_count_ok\": true,\n    \"material_ratio_notes\": [\"string\"],\n    \"openings_present\": true,\n    \"entrance_present\": true,\n    \"issues\": [\"string\"]\n  },\n  \"notes\": [\"optional\"]\n}\n\nHard constraints:\n- Coordinates must be integers.\n- Keep bbox near origin; prefer non-negative coordinates.\n- operations count <= 260.\n- Building must include floor, walls, roof, windows, entrance.\n- Use normalized material IDs where possible.\n- Every operation must lie inside bbox.\n\nDesign quality rules:\n- Prioritize global silhouette correctness first, then openings, then small details.\n- Avoid fragmented micro-operations when one larger cuboid works.\n- Keep openings aligned and symmetric when description indicates symmetry.\n- If uncertain, choose coherent defaults and note uncertainty in notes/self_check. \n\nReference examples (few-shot):\n[[FEW_SHOTS]]\n\nNow produce a plan for this input:\nDescription JSON:\n[[DESCRIPTION_JSON]]",
  "critic_system_prompt": "You are a strict Minecraft plan reviewer. Output only one corrected final JSON object. No markdown.",
  "critic_user_template": "You must revise a draft build plan to maximize executability and fidelity.\n\nTasks:\n1) Validate bbox integrity and ensure all operation coordinates are inside bbox.\n2) Validate operation count <= 260.\n3) Validate the plan contains floor, walls, roof, windows, and an entrance opening.\n4) Check material coherence (wall/roof/trim/glass/floor roles are not collapsed to one block unless justified).\n5) Improve structural faithfulness: footprint, floor layering, openings, roof profile.\n6) Fill self_check fields honestly after revision.\n\nReturn FINAL corrected JSON only (same schema as planner output).\n\nDescription JSON:\n[[DESCRIPTION_JSON]]\n\nDraft Plan JSON:\n[[DRAFT_PLAN_JSON]]",
